article.headline: Southern Miss 64, Tulane 58
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Jarekus Singleton scored 19 points and Charles Gaines had 17 points and 13 rebounds as Southern Mississippi beat Tulane 64-58 Saturday night. Southern Miss (10-8, 3-4 Conference USA) used a 10-0 run to take a 42-34 lead with 12:45 to go in the game. Tulane (7-10, 0-6) came back on four free throws and a 3-pointer by Chris Moore to cut the Golden Eagles' lead to 42-41 with 9:46 left. A 9-4 run by Southern Miss iced the victory. Marcus Kinzer matched his career-high with 17 points for Tulane. Kory Castine and Wayne Tinsley each added 10 points. Castine also had 10 rebounds.
